{{Infobox scientist |name = Olaf Mertelsmann |image = <!--(filename only)--> |image_size = |caption = |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1969|01|15|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Germany]] |death_date = |death_place = |nationality = {{flag|Germany}} |fields = [[History]] |workplaces = [[University of Tartu]] |alma_mater = [[University of Hamburg]] |academic_advisors = |notable_students = |influences = |influenced = |awards = }} '''Olaf Mertelsmann''' (born 15 January 1969) is a [[Germans|German]] historian and a professor at the [[University of Tartu]]. Dr. Mertelsmann's primary interest is the [[history of the Soviet Union]], with concentration on [[post-war]] period. He has been living in [[Estonia]] since 1994.
