[[Silla]] (57 BC – 935 CE) was one of the [[Three Kingdoms of Korea]]. In the early years, Silla was ruled by the [[Park (Korean name)|Pak]], [[Seok (Korean name)|Seok]], and [[Kim (Korean name)|Kim]] families. Rulers of Silla had various titles, including ''Isageum, Maripgan, and Daewang''. Like some Baekje kings, some declared themselves emperor.

